WEBVTT

00:01.080 --> 00:02.411
NICK: Previously on Grimm...

00:02.520 --> 00:04.010
Your child is very active.

00:04.440 --> 00:06.408
That means it will not be long.

00:06.480 --> 00:07.720
ADALIND: It's only
been six months.

00:07.800 --> 00:09.211
(SCREAMING)

00:10.400 --> 00:11.890
We must get you into hiding.

00:12.000 --> 00:14.606
We must not arouse the
suspicion of Prince Viktor.

00:14.880 --> 00:17.167
RENARD: We've linked this
attack to two other scalpings.

00:17.320 --> 00:18.810
Seems we have a serial killer

00:18.880 --> 00:20.370
who's targeting men in uniform.

00:20.480 --> 00:22.642
"The Wildesheer scalp
their defeated enemies.

00:22.840 --> 00:25.684
"They sew these trophies of
war into cloaks of hair,

00:25.760 --> 00:28.525
"supposedly giving them the power
of the warriors they've defeated."

00:29.120 --> 00:30.565
Will you marry me?
(CLOCK CHIMING)

00:30.680 --> 00:33.604
Will you?
Yes. I mean, I will.

00:33.800 --> 00:34.801
This is our wedding.

00:34.880 --> 00:37.201
Everybody has to accept
everybody for who they are.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.161
BOTH: Surprise!

00:39.240 --> 00:40.287
Mom, Dad.

00:40.440 --> 00:41.480
(WHISPERING) Your parents?

00:41.520 --> 00:42.521
Don't worry.
It's gonna be fine.

00:42.640 --> 00:43.641
Come here.

00:44.080 --> 00:45.286
(GROANS)

00:45.800 --> 00:47.165
No, no, no, no.

00:47.640 --> 00:48.801
A Fuchsbau?

00:48.880 --> 00:50.166
What the hell is going on here?

00:50.240 --> 00:51.401
This is never going to work.

00:51.640 --> 00:53.802
I cannot listen to this ignorance.
I'm leaving.

00:53.920 --> 00:55.843
Rosalee... No. I need
some time with this.

00:56.040 --> 00:57.326
Oh, Nick. Crap.

00:57.960 --> 00:59.485
A Grimm!

00:59.640 --> 01:01.165
Mom, Dad, no!
(GROWLING)

01:01.400 --> 01:02.765
No!

01:04.040 --> 01:06.247
(GROWLING)
MONROE: No! Stop!

01:07.360 --> 01:09.840
(GLASS SHATTERS)
Not in my house!

01:09.920 --> 01:11.046
(GRUNTING)

01:11.560 --> 01:13.961
Nick, Dad, stop!

01:14.400 --> 01:15.811
(GRUNTING)
(GROWLING)

01:15.880 --> 01:17.291
Mom, no!
He's a friend of mine!

01:17.480 --> 01:19.482
(BOTH GROWLING) No, no, no, no, no!
Stop!

01:19.920 --> 01:22.321
Everybody, stop!
Nick is a friend.

01:25.320 --> 01:27.322
A friend? What the
hell is going on here?

01:27.480 --> 01:30.370
Nick, these are my parents.

01:30.520 --> 01:31.567
He's a Grimm!

01:31.640 --> 01:33.369
You're friends with a Grimm?

01:33.440 --> 01:35.568
Yes.
I am so sorry.

01:36.320 --> 01:38.641
I really didn't want to hit you.

01:40.160 --> 01:41.764
Although, they did
just try to kill me.

01:41.840 --> 01:43.808
Let me try and understand
something here.

01:44.280 --> 01:46.248
You're Blutbaden.
I'm Blutbaden.

01:46.320 --> 01:48.004
Your mother's Blutbaden.

01:48.160 --> 01:49.207
He's a Grimm...

01:49.280 --> 01:50.281
I can explain.

01:50.360 --> 01:51.640
And you let him into your house.

01:51.680 --> 01:53.887
Did you not hear what I just said?
Nick is a friend.

01:53.960 --> 01:56.361
(SCOFFS) First he's
engaged to a Fuchsbau,

01:56.760 --> 01:58.888
then he becomes friends
with a Grimm.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.246
(SNARLS)
MONROE: No, no, no!

02:00.400 --> 02:03.051
That is not happening.
Not in my house.

02:03.160 --> 02:06.130
Well, maybe your Grimm friend
would like to take it outside.

02:06.200 --> 02:08.008
No, he would not like
to take it outside,

02:08.080 --> 02:10.287
because he'll kill you, okay?

02:10.400 --> 02:12.402
I've seen it happen.
I've seen him do it.

02:12.720 --> 02:14.961
You've hunted with a Grimm?

02:15.360 --> 02:17.283
He's a cop.
I mean, I just...

02:17.360 --> 02:18.850
Alice, we're leaving.

02:19.720 --> 02:22.291
Look, I don't want to cause
any problems here.

02:22.400 --> 02:24.289
A little late for that.
Please, just...

02:24.360 --> 02:26.408
Why don't you just shut up?

02:26.720 --> 02:30.486
I don't know what you two are
doing here, but it's wrong.

02:32.600 --> 02:33.840
Mom!

02:34.920 --> 02:37.605
I don't even know
who you are anymore.

02:38.400 --> 02:39.925
(DOOR SLAMS)

02:44.240 --> 02:48.723
Monroe, lam sorry.
I had no idea.

02:48.920 --> 02:50.285
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

02:51.200 --> 02:52.690
Why did you come over?

02:52.760 --> 02:54.205
I...

02:56.360 --> 03:00.081
Just never mind.
Nick, what do you want?

03:01.600 --> 03:02.761
I wanted help on a case.

03:02.840 --> 03:04.080
Yeah, no, that's what I figured,

03:04.120 --> 03:07.920
'cause that's what
Monroe is good for.

03:08.680 --> 03:09.841
Oh, Monroe, you know
that's not true.

03:09.960 --> 03:11.689
I'm not so sure I do.

03:12.280 --> 03:14.408
Well, I can see that
now is not a good time.

03:14.480 --> 03:15.970
Not very.

03:17.800 --> 03:19.370
I'll call you.

03:24.120 --> 03:25.406
(DOOR OPENS)

03:28.120 --> 03:29.451
(BELL JINGLES)

03:34.480 --> 03:35.686
(SOBBING)

04:04.520 --> 04:06.329
NICK: Maybe I do count
on Monroe too much.

04:06.840 --> 04:09.764
If he had a problem helping you, he
would have stopped a long time ago.

04:10.160 --> 04:12.162
This isn't about that.

04:13.240 --> 04:14.480
Maybe you're right.

04:14.560 --> 04:17.370
But I should stop asking
him for help for a while.

04:17.560 --> 04:19.244
What did you want
to talk to him about?

04:19.760 --> 04:21.841
We've got a killer
scalping victims.

04:22.400 --> 04:25.244
We think it's Wesen.

04:25.560 --> 04:27.562
Whoa.
Yeah.

04:30.720 --> 04:31.767
(SIGHS)

05:26.280 --> 05:27.566
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

05:27.720 --> 05:28.846
Yes?

05:28.920 --> 05:30.081
SEBASTIEN:
Prince Viktor?

05:32.440 --> 05:34.761
Stefania Vaduva Popescu is here.

05:38.080 --> 05:40.560
Your Highness.

05:40.640 --> 05:42.847
Things seem to be
moving right along.

05:42.920 --> 05:45.127
Faster than I expected.

05:45.320 --> 05:47.766
How much longer do we have?

05:47.840 --> 05:49.842
A few days at most.

05:55.160 --> 05:56.685
What is she sucking on?

05:57.560 --> 05:59.369
STEFANIA:
Mandrake root.

05:59.880 --> 06:02.247
I gave it to her
to slow things down.

06:02.560 --> 06:04.881
But if you want the child
born in the castle,

06:04.960 --> 06:06.962
then I suggest we move quickly.

06:07.920 --> 06:10.161
We shall wait no longer.

06:10.680 --> 06:12.808
Stefania Vaduva
Popescu is in the castle.

06:13.680 --> 06:14.761
Are you sure?

06:15.400 --> 06:17.243
She's meeting with
the prince now.

06:17.520 --> 06:18.681
Do you know her?

06:18.760 --> 06:21.047
I know of her.
My mother knew her well.

06:22.280 --> 06:24.248
She's the biggest
black marketeer over there.

06:24.600 --> 06:26.090
Do we know if she's had
any contact with Adalind?

06:26.160 --> 06:27.286
No, we don't.

06:28.280 --> 06:30.965
We do know that Adalind and Frau
Pech were working together.

06:31.040 --> 06:32.690
Frau Pech is probably dead.

06:32.960 --> 06:35.167
This explains how Ada/ind
is getting her powers back.

06:36.320 --> 06:38.641
And now Stefania
is betraying Adalind

06:39.160 --> 06:41.481
and brokering the child
to the Royal Family herself.

06:41.720 --> 06:42.881
What do you want me to do?

06:43.080 --> 06:45.003
I want you to get to
Ada/ind before they do.

06:45.200 --> 06:46.690
We have no time to wait.

06:47.280 --> 06:49.487
You have to meet with Meisner, tonight.
I'll set it up from here.

06:49.640 --> 06:50.846
What if I can't get away?

06:51.000 --> 06:53.606
Then find an excuse. Fake your
own death for all I care.

06:53.720 --> 06:55.882
Do not let them get
to Ada/ind first.

06:56.000 --> 06:57.047
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

06:57.120 --> 06:58.724
I have to go. Yeah?
(DOOR OPENS)

06:58.880 --> 07:00.769
Captain, we've got
new intel on our cop killer.

07:00.840 --> 07:01.841
Oh, yeah? What is it?

07:01.920 --> 07:03.285
HANK: We canvassed
every bank and business

07:03.400 --> 07:04.925
with a surveillance camera
in a three-block radius

07:05.000 --> 07:06.923
of the hotel where
the killer was staying.

07:07.080 --> 07:09.048
And we got bupkis
on the suspect.

07:09.120 --> 07:11.930
However, a bank camera
caught footage of students

07:12.000 --> 07:14.128
from Lewis & Clark College
shooting a film.

07:14.280 --> 07:15.691
Their camera happened
to be shooting

07:15.760 --> 07:17.683
across the street from
the hotel parking lot

07:17.840 --> 07:19.808
when our suspect stole
the '97 Chevy pickup.

07:19.880 --> 07:21.450
Which is why it took a
little time to track down.

07:21.640 --> 07:22.641
This is what they got.

07:26.680 --> 07:27.806
Seriously?

07:27.880 --> 07:28.961
Just watch.

07:30.480 --> 07:31.970
(TAPPING KEYS)

07:32.160 --> 07:33.286
HANK: Not much
of his face.

07:33.360 --> 07:34.771
Still, those are the
first visuals we've got

07:34.840 --> 07:35.840
on this son of a bitch.

07:35.880 --> 07:37.723
All right, get this out
to all the agencies, now.

07:37.800 --> 07:39.245
Yes, sir.

07:41.880 --> 07:42.927
(DOOR CLOSES)

07:44.920 --> 07:46.285
(LOCK CLICKING)
(KEYS JINGLING)

07:46.400 --> 07:47.640
(BELL JINGLES)

07:50.960 --> 07:52.121
(DOOR CLOSES)

07:58.840 --> 08:00.046
(SIGHS)

08:00.320 --> 08:01.765
I am so sorry.

08:03.720 --> 08:05.609
If I had known,

08:05.680 --> 08:07.569
I never would have
told them anything.

08:08.400 --> 08:09.447
We need to talk.

08:21.120 --> 08:24.090
I love you.

08:24.240 --> 08:25.605
I love you. But...

08:26.040 --> 08:28.646
lam not gonna let my parents
destroy the best thing

08:28.720 --> 08:30.085
that's ever happened to me.

08:30.360 --> 08:31.441
It's not that easy.

08:31.840 --> 08:33.967
This will ruin your
relationship with your parents,

08:34.039 --> 08:36.159
and I'm not quite sure I want
to be the cause of that.

08:36.200 --> 08:37.201
You're not.

08:37.280 --> 08:40.169
They're the cause of it.
Monroe, I lost my dad.

08:40.240 --> 08:42.686
I didn't speak to my mom
or sister for seven years.

08:42.760 --> 08:44.967
This is not an easy thing to do.

08:45.520 --> 08:46.931
You will regret it.

08:47.520 --> 08:49.170
And then you're gonna regret me.

08:49.400 --> 08:50.606
Never

08:53.600 --> 08:57.844
I don't believe what
they believe, okay?

08:58.280 --> 09:01.329
And if that destroys my
relationship with them, so be it.

09:07.840 --> 09:10.525
And besides,

09:10.920 --> 09:12.160
it's not just you.

09:12.560 --> 09:15.291
What?
Nick came over.

09:15.560 --> 09:18.291
Oh, my God.
Did they Woge?

09:18.360 --> 09:19.486
Both of 'em.

09:19.800 --> 09:22.167
Just before they attacked Nick.

09:23.720 --> 09:27.008
So, now they know you're
friends with a Grimm

09:27.320 --> 09:28.924
and you want to
marry a Fuchsbau.

09:29.000 --> 09:30.490
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

09:30.720 --> 09:32.131
(SIGHS)

09:33.200 --> 09:36.568
I guess you could say
I'm a disappointment.

09:38.480 --> 09:39.481
(SCOFFS)

09:51.840 --> 09:54.127
Jackson Quarry,
dispatch from Officer Mart.

09:54.520 --> 09:56.761
DISPATCHER: Jackson Quarry,
Officer Mart. Go ahead.

09:57.640 --> 10:02.202
I'm investigating a fire,
2.7 miles up road 43b.

10:02.800 --> 10:04.131
Is the fire contained?

10:04.680 --> 10:07.047
Appears to be.
I'm gonna check it out.

10:14.800 --> 10:17.087
Looks like an illegal campsite.

10:17.800 --> 10:19.564
Maybe some poaching.

10:20.400 --> 10:21.811
Do you need support,
Officer Mart?

10:21.880 --> 10:23.769
No, let me see what
I've got here first.

10:23.880 --> 10:25.769
I'm not sure anybody's
even still around.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.365
Roger that.

10:39.360 --> 10:40.691
(SNIFFS) Oh...

10:47.240 --> 10:49.481
I think I might be
onto something here.

10:49.560 --> 10:53.246
I've got two vehicles,
one, an older Chevy pickup,

10:54.000 --> 10:55.843
the other's a Jeep.

10:55.960 --> 10:57.325
The Chevy's licensed
out of Oregon,

10:57.400 --> 11:00.085
E-B-S-7-7-5.

11:00.240 --> 11:04.450
The Jeep, license
Kansas, D-A-D-8-1-7.

11:04.920 --> 11:06.843
What was the make on that
vehicle we got the report

11:06.920 --> 11:07.967
from on Portland PD?

11:08.800 --> 11:10.723
Hold on, let me check.

11:13.080 --> 11:15.890
A stolen 1997
Chevy Silverado pickup.

11:16.120 --> 11:17.804
Driver is considered
extremely dangerous.

11:17.880 --> 11:20.281
You are advised not to confront
the suspect without support.

11:20.360 --> 11:21.725
Sending backup immediately.

11:31.440 --> 11:33.886
You need to put your hands
behind your head.

11:35.440 --> 11:36.441
(THUDS)

11:37.920 --> 11:39.126
(GROWLING)

11:40.360 --> 11:41.885
(SCREAMING)

11:44.840 --> 11:46.524
Officer Mart, come in.

11:46.640 --> 11:48.051
Officer Mart?

11:59.440 --> 12:00.805
(SIGHS)

12:02.800 --> 12:04.290
You Okay?

12:04.360 --> 12:06.966
(SIGHS) I just
remembered where we are,

12:08.560 --> 12:10.483
and where we should be,

12:10.880 --> 12:12.882
and why we're not there.

12:13.840 --> 12:15.888
What time is it?

12:18.280 --> 12:19.486
6228.

12:19.560 --> 12:21.210
Oh, no, it's too early.

12:24.120 --> 12:27.010
No. It's too late.

12:27.720 --> 12:29.245
I gotta go deal with this.

12:29.320 --> 12:30.321
Monroe...

12:30.440 --> 12:32.488
Nobody talks to you that way.

12:36.120 --> 12:38.407
Who you calling?
My mother.

12:39.920 --> 12:42.446
I'm gonna find them,
say my goodbyes,

12:42.680 --> 12:43.681
(SIGHS)

12:43.760 --> 12:46.525
and we're gonna get on
with our life together.

12:48.000 --> 12:49.445
(RINGING)

12:55.320 --> 12:56.321
Monroe?

12:56.440 --> 12:58.602
I think I should come over
and we should talk.

12:58.880 --> 12:59.881
Where are you?

13:00.000 --> 13:01.490
The Stanbridge Hotel.

13:02.080 --> 13:05.050
Okay. I'll be there soon.

13:07.120 --> 13:09.043
He's coming over to talk.

13:09.120 --> 13:11.726
I hope he's got a lot
to say, 'cause I don't.

13:12.880 --> 13:13.881
(GRUNTS)

13:16.720 --> 13:18.165
NICK: I hope those
aren't more taxes.

13:18.240 --> 13:21.687
No. After having delightful
nightmares about being scalped,

13:21.760 --> 13:23.125
I thought I would
find out as much

13:23.200 --> 13:24.560
as I could about
why somebody would

13:24.600 --> 13:26.523
want to do this to me
while I was sleeping.

13:27.240 --> 13:28.241
You interested?

13:28.560 --> 13:29.561
What have you got?
Okay.

13:29.640 --> 13:32.166
This dates back
to the Scythians.

13:32.240 --> 13:35.369
That's like 44 BC.
The Scythians would hang

13:35.440 --> 13:37.204
their victims' scalps
from their bridles.

13:37.280 --> 13:39.009
Apparently, they were
very proud of them.

13:39.080 --> 13:41.526
The more they had, the bigger and
badder they supposedly were.

13:41.600 --> 13:44.171
There are a ton of
historical references,

13:44.240 --> 13:46.846
like the Sachsenspiegel,
which was the most important

13:46.920 --> 13:48.843
law book of the Germanic
Middle Ages.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.809
The book said that
the men who were convicted

13:50.880 --> 13:53.008
of the most heinous crimes
were sentenced

13:53.080 --> 13:55.401
to have their heads scalped
because hair was considered

13:55.520 --> 13:57.090
a mystical symbol
of the free man.

13:57.560 --> 13:59.210
Anyway, the gist of all this is,

13:59.280 --> 14:01.647
the more scalps you have, the
more power you've extracted

14:01.720 --> 14:03.000
from your enemies
and the fiercer

14:03.040 --> 14:04.280
you therefore were
on the battlefield.

14:04.480 --> 14:06.562
And that part makes sense.

14:07.080 --> 14:08.491
Hank and I were in the trailer,

14:08.560 --> 14:10.085
and we think the guy we're after

14:10.200 --> 14:12.521
is using these scalps
to make a cloak.

14:13.160 --> 14:14.400
So this is Wesen?

14:14.480 --> 14:15.560
That's what we're thinking.

14:15.600 --> 14:17.204
Nick, if this guy
is targeting police...

14:17.280 --> 14:19.123
Yeah, I know.
I'll watch my hair.

14:19.200 --> 14:20.964
No, this is serious!

14:21.880 --> 14:23.086
You're a cop,
and you're a Grimm.

14:23.160 --> 14:25.640
If this guy finds out
you're here...

14:26.200 --> 14:28.487
Wesen have come
after you before.

14:28.960 --> 14:31.804
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
I know. Don't worry.

14:33.280 --> 14:34.441
Burkhardt.

14:35.520 --> 14:37.090
Where was the body found?

14:37.960 --> 14:39.291
Another one in uniform.

14:39.720 --> 14:41.210
I'll meet you at the precinct.

14:42.440 --> 14:44.647
There's another one?
Yeah.

14:54.160 --> 14:55.400
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

14:56.280 --> 14:57.327
He's here.

14:57.400 --> 14:59.289
Maybe he's finally
come to his senses.

15:03.640 --> 15:04.641
Morning.

15:15.320 --> 15:16.481
(SIGHS)

15:17.000 --> 15:19.367
Maybe it's my fault. I should
have told you about Rosalee.

15:19.480 --> 15:20.527
Yes, you should have.

15:21.040 --> 15:23.520
I didn't know you were
gonna come out right away.

15:23.680 --> 15:26.081
Okay? I thought I had
a little more time.

15:26.160 --> 15:27.810
But I should have
said something, okay?

15:27.880 --> 15:29.166
But that shouldn't even matter.

15:29.360 --> 15:31.089
It does matter!

15:31.200 --> 15:32.725
These mixed marriages
never work.

15:32.840 --> 15:35.320
We are not living 100 years ago.

15:35.400 --> 15:37.562
There is reasons
we stick to these rules.

15:37.680 --> 15:40.286
Yeah. Ignorance
and bigotry.

15:40.840 --> 15:42.604
Bart, let him talk.

15:42.680 --> 15:44.887
I don't have to
let him do anything.

15:45.880 --> 15:48.121
And I can't believe you're still
doing this vegetarian crap.

15:48.200 --> 15:50.282
Why don't you just
wear a sign saying

15:50.360 --> 15:51.771
you're ashamed of who you are?

15:52.000 --> 15:53.126
I'm not ashamed of anything.

15:53.200 --> 15:54.770
BART: Oh, yeah,
I saw that

15:54.840 --> 15:56.604
with you and your Grimm.

15:56.720 --> 15:58.290
(SCOFFS) Are you serious?

15:58.360 --> 15:59.691
Nick is different.

15:59.760 --> 16:01.489
Oh, he's a vegetarian too?

16:01.960 --> 16:03.200
(SNARLING)

16:04.920 --> 16:06.046
Mmm.

16:09.440 --> 16:10.441
(SIGHS)

16:12.040 --> 16:17.524
Look, I just came to say that
I'm sorry you don't care

16:17.600 --> 16:19.887
to understand who I am

16:19.960 --> 16:22.361
or listen to anything
that I have to say.

16:23.400 --> 16:26.210
But I love Rosalee,
and I'm gonna marry her,

16:26.320 --> 16:29.324
and if that destroys
the family, then so be it.

16:29.400 --> 16:31.164
Oh, please don't say that.

16:31.240 --> 16:32.844
You're not giving me any choice.

16:32.920 --> 16:35.127
You just refuse
to respect who we are.

16:38.920 --> 16:41.161
I'm sorry you feel that way.

16:43.600 --> 16:45.602
(SNIFFLES) Goodbye.

16:49.240 --> 16:50.446
(SIGHS)

16:51.440 --> 16:52.487
What have we done?

16:52.760 --> 16:54.922
The right thing.

17:07.119 --> 17:08.281
(SNIFFS)

17:10.359 --> 17:11.566
(PHONE RINGS)

17:11.960 --> 17:13.121
(GASPS)

17:23.960 --> 17:26.122
Why are you calling me
in the middle of the night?

17:26.280 --> 17:28.647
They're coming to get you. Who?

17:28.760 --> 17:30.091
Viktor is sending Verrat agents

17:30.160 --> 17:31.525
to take you back to the castle,

17:31.600 --> 17:33.489
and once you're there,
you'll never leave.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.006
How do you know that?

17:35.080 --> 17:36.969
Because your friend Stefania
was at the castle.

17:37.200 --> 17:39.771
She's betrayed you. She
works for Viktor, not you.

17:39.840 --> 17:41.569
Why should I trust you?

17:42.480 --> 17:45.723
Because I believe the child you're
carrying is mine, not Eric's.

17:45.960 --> 17:48.440
Viktor wants the child, not you.

17:48.760 --> 17:50.410
What am I supposed to do?

17:50.720 --> 17:52.688
Meisner is on his way,
with Sebastien.

17:52.880 --> 17:54.769
Sebastien?
Yeah, he works for me.

17:54.960 --> 17:56.849
Now, I suggest you leave with
them as quickly as you can.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.251
They are your only chance.

17:58.440 --> 17:59.680
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

18:00.480 --> 18:01.891
Someone's at the door.

18:02.440 --> 18:03.720
You remember
when I once told you

18:03.760 --> 18:05.762
you would have to choose a side?

18:05.840 --> 18:07.763
Well, this is the time.

18:10.080 --> 18:11.161
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

18:11.240 --> 18:12.526
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

18:22.200 --> 18:24.168
You must leave immediately.
Get dressed.

18:24.400 --> 18:26.687
SEBASTIEN: I will watch
from downstairs.

18:27.000 --> 18:28.570
Hurry!

18:28.840 --> 18:30.808
I'm pregnant.
I can't go that fast.

18:30.920 --> 18:32.763
Do you want to live?
Yes.

18:33.160 --> 18:35.766
Then put on a coat and put
some clothes in a bag.

18:39.720 --> 18:40.721
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

18:42.720 --> 18:43.767
Yeah?

18:43.840 --> 18:46.969
SEBASTIEN: Two Verrat are on their way up.
There may be more.

18:48.360 --> 18:50.249
Okay, we have to go now.
The Verrat are here.

18:50.320 --> 18:51.446
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

18:57.280 --> 19:00.727
Okay, answer the door.
Tell them you're not alone.

19:01.920 --> 19:03.046
But what if they come in?

19:03.200 --> 19:07.250
That's exactly what
I want them to do.

19:09.520 --> 19:10.521
Go.

19:12.640 --> 19:13.926
Go!

19:23.120 --> 19:25.930
Fraulein Schade. Prince Viktor
requests your presence.

19:26.400 --> 19:28.164
At this time of night?

19:28.280 --> 19:30.760
Yes.
MAN: Adalind, who is it?

19:42.040 --> 19:43.530
These men want me
to go with them.

19:43.600 --> 19:45.011
Who the hell are you?

19:45.480 --> 19:47.562
What is your name?
What is my name?

19:47.840 --> 19:50.844
Well, excuse me, this isn't your room.
What is your name?

19:51.440 --> 19:52.521
Get up.

19:52.600 --> 19:54.364
Please, he's just a friend.

19:54.440 --> 19:55.441
(GROANING)

20:00.800 --> 20:01.926
Do you work for the hotel?

20:02.000 --> 20:03.126
I won't ask again.

20:03.280 --> 20:04.486
ADALIND: Oh, God.

20:06.280 --> 20:08.044
Get up now.

20:10.520 --> 20:11.646
(SILENCED GUNSHOT)
(GROANS)

20:15.400 --> 20:16.401
(EXCLAIMS)

20:26.920 --> 20:27.921
(THANKS IN GERMAN)

20:29.160 --> 20:30.605
I'm not sure that was me.

20:30.680 --> 20:32.603
Let's get out of here.

20:39.520 --> 20:42.171
WU: Not a good way to start the day.
Where's the body?

20:42.320 --> 20:45.767
Over there. Some of it. Body's
kind of all over the place.

20:46.440 --> 20:48.920
Victim is Thomas Mart, works
for the Forest Service.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.280
Checking out an illegal campfire

20:50.320 --> 20:51.845
where a deer was poached,

20:52.200 --> 20:54.680
reported it, was
investigating, call went dead.

20:55.000 --> 20:56.445
They sent out a team
to investigate and found

20:56.520 --> 20:58.170
the Chevy pickup
we've been looking for,

20:58.240 --> 20:59.844
the one stolen from
the hotel manager.

21:00.000 --> 21:02.048
Mart also reported
seeing a Jeep here.

21:02.520 --> 21:03.806
Kansas plates.

21:03.880 --> 21:06.008
We got an APB out on it.

21:06.080 --> 21:08.447
That would be Mart's right arm.

21:08.520 --> 21:10.443
Left leg is over there
in two pieces.

21:10.520 --> 21:12.648
Looks like animals got
to him after the attack.

21:12.720 --> 21:14.882
Anyway, I hope so.

21:15.000 --> 21:17.128
I'd hate to think this happened
to him while he was alive.

21:17.200 --> 21:19.282
You said there were two
cars reported. Yeah.

21:19.360 --> 21:20.885
He couldn't have
driven both cars here.

21:21.160 --> 21:22.720
That means there's
more than one killer.

21:35.400 --> 21:36.890
Why are you helping me?

21:36.960 --> 21:39.122
You and your child are
very important to us.

21:39.200 --> 21:41.043
We work with the Resistance.

21:41.120 --> 21:42.804
So does Sean Renard.

21:42.880 --> 21:44.769
Frau Pech came to me months ago,

21:44.840 --> 21:47.127
offering to sell your child
to the Royal Family.

21:47.240 --> 21:49.971
MAN: We are not going
to let that happen.

21:51.640 --> 21:53.608
Pull over.
This is good.

21:53.840 --> 21:55.410
In the middle of nowhere?

21:55.560 --> 21:58.245
Well, it's better if you don't
know where we have gone.

22:09.360 --> 22:10.646
What do you expect me to do?

22:10.760 --> 22:11.761
Walk.

22:14.640 --> 22:15.641
(SCOFFS)

22:18.320 --> 22:19.606
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

22:32.400 --> 22:34.448
Now what?
It's freezing.

22:38.280 --> 22:40.282
You will warm up as we go.

22:49.280 --> 22:50.361
(BELL JINGLES)

22:51.640 --> 22:52.721
Hey.

22:52.800 --> 22:53.881
Juliette.

22:54.440 --> 22:56.408
How are you doing?

22:56.520 --> 22:59.569
Oh, a pleasant mixture
of sadness, anger,

22:59.640 --> 23:01.449
resentment, and bitterness.

23:01.960 --> 23:03.689
Nick told me.
I'm so sorry.

23:03.800 --> 23:05.131
That's why I came over.
I didn't know if maybe

23:05.200 --> 23:07.009
you wanted a shoulder
to pound on.

23:07.080 --> 23:09.048
Oh, thanks.
How's Nick doing?

23:09.120 --> 23:11.487
I heard he had his own meet and
greet with Monroe's parents.

23:11.680 --> 23:13.967
He feels really bad about that.

23:14.080 --> 23:17.163
Monroe was in no place to
deal with anybody last night.

23:17.320 --> 23:19.209
What did Nick need?
Maybe I can help.

23:19.320 --> 23:22.290
It is the most terrifying
series of murders,

23:22.360 --> 23:23.691
and the worst part is,

23:23.760 --> 23:26.331
the killer has been
scalping his victims.

23:26.400 --> 23:27.765
Anyway, Nick thinks it's Wesen,

23:27.840 --> 23:29.046
but why am I telling
you this right now?

23:29.120 --> 23:30.246
You don't need
to hear about this.

23:30.320 --> 23:31.526
The victims were scalped?

23:31.600 --> 23:33.204
Yeah.
(BELL JINGLES)

23:36.240 --> 23:37.401
Hey, Juliette.

23:37.520 --> 23:39.284
Hey, Monroe.
How did it go?

23:40.240 --> 23:41.890
Let's just say it went.

23:42.800 --> 23:45.041
I feel really bad about what
happened to Nick last night.

23:45.160 --> 23:47.128
Some of the things I said...
It's okay.

23:47.200 --> 23:49.441
Monroe, he feels
really awful too.

23:49.800 --> 23:51.529
Did Nick tell you
why he stopped by?

23:51.640 --> 23:54.530
No, no, my folks kind of
got in the way of that.

23:54.600 --> 23:57.285
Somebody is murdering
people and scalping them.

23:57.360 --> 23:58.691
Nick thinks it's Wesen.

23:59.520 --> 24:02.524
That's not why I came by,
just so we're all clear.

24:02.680 --> 24:03.806
Caccia Morta?

24:04.760 --> 24:06.125
But it can't be, could it?

24:06.200 --> 24:07.804
I mean, that's what
it sounds like.

24:07.880 --> 24:09.769
If it is, that's really serious.

24:09.880 --> 24:11.405
I've got to talk to Nick.

24:12.200 --> 24:13.326
(DOOR OPENS)
(BELL JINGLES)

24:14.120 --> 24:16.521
HANK: Nick, got the registration
of the Kansas plates.

24:16.680 --> 24:19.331
The Jeep is registered to
a Walter Murphy from Wichita.

24:19.400 --> 24:20.447
Is he a cop?

24:20.560 --> 24:22.369
Corporal, US. Army.

24:22.480 --> 24:24.482
NICK: Did they find him?
HANK: No.

24:24.560 --> 24:26.881
Reported AWOL three weeks ago.

24:27.200 --> 24:29.202
Well, I don't think we're looking
for Walter Murphy from Wichita.

24:29.320 --> 24:31.288
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
I don't either.

24:35.920 --> 24:37.001
Monroe.

24:37.120 --> 24:38.565
Nick, we need to talk.

24:38.640 --> 24:40.802
Hey, I'm sorry about last night.

24:41.000 --> 24:42.331
Yeah, I'm sorry too, dude.
Really.

24:42.400 --> 24:44.641
But we got bigger Wesen to fry.

24:44.920 --> 24:46.763
Caccia Morta,
you ever heard of them?

24:46.960 --> 24:49.167
Caccia Morta. Yeah.

24:49.520 --> 24:51.170
I think we just read
about them in the trailer.

24:51.240 --> 24:52.321
That's the same thing
as Wildesheer, right?

24:52.400 --> 24:53.526
Close enough.

24:53.600 --> 24:55.250
That's why I was
coming over last night.

24:55.320 --> 24:56.401
Well, you better come over now,

24:56.480 --> 24:58.801
because this is
way more complicated

24:58.880 --> 25:00.882
than your average Wesen rampage.

25:00.960 --> 25:02.883
But just you, okay?

25:04.240 --> 25:06.925
This is too dangerous for
a Kehrseite-Schlich-Kennen.

25:07.000 --> 25:09.048
At least until we figure
out how to deal with this.

25:16.760 --> 25:17.966
This is it.

25:18.120 --> 25:19.485
Who lives here?

25:19.600 --> 25:20.601
No one.

25:20.880 --> 25:22.882
It's been in my family
for a long time.

25:29.920 --> 25:31.046
(DOOR CREAKS)

25:36.520 --> 25:38.124
I'm hungry.

25:38.240 --> 25:39.526
Oh, first, I'll start a fire,

25:39.640 --> 25:41.130
then I'll get us
something to eat.

25:41.200 --> 25:42.964
(SIGHS) We're in
the middle of nowhere.

25:43.040 --> 25:45.361
How are you... Oh.

25:45.480 --> 25:47.482
There's some bedding
in the trunk.

25:48.840 --> 25:50.126
(SIGHS)

26:01.760 --> 26:02.886
I'm ready.

26:02.960 --> 26:04.121
I'm not.

26:04.720 --> 26:05.801
What?

26:06.880 --> 26:07.927
(SIGHS)

26:09.000 --> 26:11.002
I'm not ready to lose our son.

26:11.560 --> 26:13.005
You've already lost him.

26:13.160 --> 26:14.924
Then I'm gonna
get him back again.

26:15.160 --> 26:17.003
Alice, we are leaving.

26:17.080 --> 26:18.286
I'm not going.

26:19.000 --> 26:20.001
I am.

26:21.240 --> 26:22.401
I know.

26:25.120 --> 26:26.326
Do what you want.

26:27.480 --> 26:29.767
You know, I think
I will for a change.

26:36.160 --> 26:37.525
(SIGHS)
(DOOR SHUTS)

26:40.800 --> 26:42.131
(GRUNTING)

26:54.040 --> 26:55.121
Why am I here?

26:55.480 --> 26:58.245
VIKTOR: Because
Adalind is not.

26:58.320 --> 26:59.481
You didn't get her?

27:00.160 --> 27:03.369
Apparently, someone tipped
them off and they escaped.

27:04.200 --> 27:06.089
You let them get away?

27:06.160 --> 27:09.881
It is my instinct to blame
you for this treachery.

27:11.680 --> 27:13.125
I came here.

27:13.200 --> 27:14.247
I told you it was time.

27:14.360 --> 27:16.089
Perhaps you're getting
more money elsewhere.

27:16.560 --> 27:18.403
I am not an idiot.

27:18.680 --> 27:20.523
I wouldn't betray you.

27:20.720 --> 27:22.370
If we've been betrayed,

27:22.440 --> 27:24.761
then it's coming from
your house, not mine.

27:27.560 --> 27:30.609
Someone close to you
has betrayed us both.

27:43.840 --> 27:45.171
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

27:45.600 --> 27:47.489
Rosalee, it's Alice.

27:47.720 --> 27:49.484
Are you still here?

27:51.000 --> 27:52.729
Now what? (SIGHS)

27:58.720 --> 28:00.404
I need to talk to you.

28:01.920 --> 28:03.206
(SIGHS)

28:03.720 --> 28:04.926
(BELL JINGLES)

28:06.080 --> 28:07.286
Thank you.

28:09.680 --> 28:10.681
(SIGHS)

28:15.320 --> 28:17.243
Quite a shop you have here.

28:17.640 --> 28:19.802
I don't think you came
to talk about my shop.

28:21.280 --> 28:22.964
No, I didn't.

28:24.560 --> 28:26.005
If you have something to say...

28:26.960 --> 28:29.440
I love my son,

28:29.560 --> 28:31.642
and I don't want to lose him.

28:32.480 --> 28:33.561
(SIGHS)

28:33.640 --> 28:35.529
Clearly, he loves you,

28:36.960 --> 28:39.440
and I hope to God you love him.

28:42.960 --> 28:44.530
I do. Very much.

28:47.920 --> 28:48.967
Lookâ€œ.

28:51.880 --> 28:55.009
You two have to decide
for yourselves what's right.

28:56.160 --> 28:58.003
Even if it's a mistake.

28:59.560 --> 29:01.961
I'm not saying that it is.

29:03.720 --> 29:05.006
(SIGHS)

29:06.560 --> 29:10.007
I can't say that I'm satisfied
with every decision I've made.

29:11.760 --> 29:13.808
But I've never challenged
our traditions

29:13.880 --> 29:17.965
because I believe in them.

29:18.600 --> 29:20.364
Why are you so sure we'll fail?

29:21.600 --> 29:23.841
Because I know
how tough marriage is,

29:23.920 --> 29:25.331
even when you're the same.

29:25.400 --> 29:28.529
Then why are you here? You
know we don't agree with you.

29:28.840 --> 29:30.683
I wanted to talk
to you to see...

29:33.320 --> 29:36.051
See if you'd be open
to the Vertrautheiten.

29:38.360 --> 29:39.521
Whoa.

29:40.680 --> 29:42.125
Do you think that would help?

29:43.040 --> 29:44.724
It couldn't hurt.

29:54.640 --> 29:55.641
(SNARLS)

30:00.960 --> 30:02.644
(BOTH PURRING)

30:27.080 --> 30:28.684
What are you doing here?

30:28.760 --> 30:31.445
I was on my way to the airport...
Uh-huh?

30:31.520 --> 30:33.648
And your mother wasn't with me.

30:34.240 --> 30:35.401
What did you do?

30:35.520 --> 30:36.681
BART: I said I was leaving.

30:36.760 --> 30:37.807
I thought she'd come with me,

30:37.880 --> 30:39.769
but she didn't.

30:40.200 --> 30:42.771
So I came here,
but she's not here either.

30:42.880 --> 30:45.451
Look, Dad, I don't
have time for this, okay?

30:45.520 --> 30:47.170
Nick is on his way
over here right now,

30:47.280 --> 30:48.930
and I don't want
another episode.

30:49.760 --> 30:51.842
The Grimm is coming here?
(SIGHS)

30:55.160 --> 30:57.128
I didn't come here to argue.

30:57.280 --> 30:59.487
Oh, what, you got
a few more cultural clichÃ©s

30:59.560 --> 31:01.005
for me to live by, or what?

31:01.480 --> 31:03.369
Dad, listen, I have no interest

31:03.440 --> 31:05.602
in trying to change
you or Mom, okay?

31:05.720 --> 31:07.370
But I do have
a very real interest

31:07.440 --> 31:09.568
in living my life my own way.

31:09.880 --> 31:10.927
I get it.

31:11.920 --> 31:14.446
But believe me, that's
not the real problem.

31:14.560 --> 31:17.086
This friendship,
if that's what you call it,

31:17.160 --> 31:19.561
with the Grimm,
it goes against everything

31:19.640 --> 31:21.483
we believe in!
You don't know Nick.

31:21.560 --> 31:24.245
Know a Grimm?
How can that be possible?

31:24.360 --> 31:25.646
The fact that
I'm standing here is proof

31:25.720 --> 31:27.643
that it is indeed possible!

31:27.840 --> 31:29.922
But I didn't plan on introducing
you to Nick right now.

31:30.000 --> 31:31.331
That just happened.

31:31.400 --> 31:33.243
And let me just say...
Let me just say...

31:33.320 --> 31:35.800
The first time I met Nick,
it didn't go so well either.

31:37.240 --> 31:38.526
(GRUNTING)

31:39.400 --> 31:40.731
(GROWLING)

31:42.520 --> 31:43.726
But you know what?

31:44.280 --> 31:46.169
We got to know each other, Dad.

31:46.400 --> 31:48.368
And we started
to trust each other.

31:48.480 --> 31:50.164
He has saved my life,

31:50.320 --> 31:51.890
and I've saved his.

31:52.480 --> 31:56.201
He is different,
and so am I, so...

31:59.400 --> 32:01.926
You know, maybe it's better
this way, just out in the open,

32:02.000 --> 32:03.081
to deal with or not.

32:03.840 --> 32:05.683
But, he's on his way
over here right now,

32:05.760 --> 32:06.761
and I'm gonna help him,

32:06.840 --> 32:07.966
like it or not.

32:10.160 --> 32:13.243
And how are you
going to help him?

32:13.560 --> 32:14.846
By killing Wesen?

32:15.000 --> 32:16.365
Is that how
you're gonna help him?

32:16.520 --> 32:18.522
I'm not asking for
your approval, Dad.

32:18.600 --> 32:20.523
Whose head are you
gonna cut off tonight?

32:21.000 --> 32:22.161
A Blutbad?

32:22.520 --> 32:23.851
A Hundjager?

32:24.280 --> 32:26.965
Even if it was a Bauerschwein...
(CAR APPROACHING)

32:27.040 --> 32:29.611
(SPITS) I wouldn't agree.

32:30.120 --> 32:31.565
Caccia Morta.

32:32.880 --> 32:34.530
The Wildesheer?
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

32:35.360 --> 32:37.727
Nick's here, Dad.
Just go home.

32:38.360 --> 32:40.442
You can't go up against
the Wildesheer.

32:40.560 --> 32:42.881
Stop telling me
what I can and cannot do.

32:43.440 --> 32:46.125
Stop worrying about me, and
start worrying about Mom.

32:51.160 --> 32:52.525
We can do this another time.

32:52.600 --> 32:54.125
Not with Wildesheer, we can't.

32:54.480 --> 32:56.881
My dad's leaving.
Come on in.

33:12.080 --> 33:13.366
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

33:17.280 --> 33:18.691
(GROWLS)

33:19.080 --> 33:20.730
(HOWLS)

33:24.920 --> 33:26.160
That sounded not so good.

33:26.240 --> 33:27.480
Yeah.

33:27.800 --> 33:30.087
He's in a not-so-good
place right now.

33:30.440 --> 33:32.240
But I'm done with that.
Nick, you need to know

33:32.280 --> 33:33.361
what you're up
against this time,

33:33.440 --> 33:35.010
because it's bad.

33:35.240 --> 33:37.686
It goes way back to something
roughly translated

33:37.760 --> 33:39.000
as "the Wild hunt."

33:39.120 --> 33:41.122
It's like the gates
of hell open up

33:41.200 --> 33:42.565
and let demons
loose on the world.

33:42.640 --> 33:44.961
So stopping these guys
sooner rather than later

33:45.240 --> 33:46.446
is kind of where it's at.

33:46.520 --> 33:47.681
We can't find them.

33:47.760 --> 33:49.091
We've got no prints,
no I.D.,

33:49.160 --> 33:51.083
no record of
where they came from.

33:51.200 --> 33:52.611
That's what
I'm trying to tell you.

33:52.960 --> 33:54.883
You don't have to find them.
According to legend,

33:54.960 --> 33:58.521
the first thing you hear
is terrible thunder

33:58.640 --> 34:00.244
and howling wind,
as if the Wildesheer

34:00.320 --> 34:01.890
are being blown
right out of hell.

34:02.320 --> 34:03.651
Not so encouraging.

34:03.720 --> 34:04.960
They're hunters,

34:05.160 --> 34:07.811
and their life's blood is built
upon killing powerful warriors.

34:07.880 --> 34:09.723
And it just so happens,
the Grimm is like

34:09.800 --> 34:11.449
the most powerful
warrior of all.

34:11.639 --> 34:13.563
See? That's the Grimm there,
in the middle.

34:14.000 --> 34:15.161
(CHUCKLING)

34:15.280 --> 34:17.043
This was one of my favorite
books when I was a kid because,

34:17.120 --> 34:18.884
you know, the Grimm
gets obliterated.

34:19.840 --> 34:23.322
But... No, that was before...
Anyway.

34:23.480 --> 34:25.402
My guess is, you're the
reason they're here.

34:25.800 --> 34:27.245
You think they know about me?

34:27.320 --> 34:29.243
I think it's no coincidence
they're in Portland.

34:29.320 --> 34:31.891
I mean, come on, there are
a lot more cop/warriors

34:31.960 --> 34:33.371
in like New York city, or...

34:33.679 --> 34:34.966
Well, don't I feel special?

34:35.040 --> 34:37.360
Listen, the most
important thing is,

34:37.480 --> 34:38.925
they will be coming after you.

34:39.000 --> 34:41.047
So what we can do is
pick where it happens.

34:41.280 --> 34:43.886
And I highly suggest
that's not my house,

34:43.960 --> 34:45.643
so we should be leaving.

34:46.520 --> 34:48.760
Isn't there anything in the
book about how to fight them?

34:49.360 --> 34:51.761
Not in that book.
They're supposed to win.

34:52.760 --> 34:53.886
(DOOR OPENS)

34:54.520 --> 34:56.329
NICK: So we pick
someplace we control.

34:56.400 --> 34:57.765
MONROE: It's got to be
wide open, you know?

34:57.840 --> 34:59.763
NICK: We can see 'em coming, but
we got to weapon up first, dude.

34:59.840 --> 35:02.047
I need more firepower
than my canines.

35:03.640 --> 35:05.051
(SIGHS)

35:05.800 --> 35:07.131
(ENGINE STARTS)

35:18.720 --> 35:20.006
MONROE: So, you know
how many there are?

35:20.080 --> 35:21.923
NICK: We think there
are at least two.

35:22.000 --> 35:23.525
MONROE: Well,
better than three.

35:25.720 --> 35:26.767
(SIGHS)

35:26.840 --> 35:27.887
Kanabo.

35:28.720 --> 35:29.926
Crossbow.

35:31.520 --> 35:32.851
Ogre gun.

35:35.000 --> 35:36.047
Listen to this.

35:37.320 --> 35:40.051
"The vile cloaks of scalped
hair they wear into battle

35:40.120 --> 35:41.963
"seem to protect them
from weapons,

35:42.040 --> 35:43.565
"making them
nearly invulnerable.

35:44.040 --> 35:46.566
"I do believe that, like Samson,

35:46.640 --> 35:47.971
"they have a weakness.

35:48.080 --> 35:50.162
"If one could take their
hair as they had taken

35:50.240 --> 35:53.084
"the hair of others,
it would weaken them.

35:53.440 --> 35:56.808
"But I was unable
to get close enough

35:56.880 --> 35:59.963
"and was forced to retreat
before I could test my theory."

36:01.680 --> 36:04.524
So we're talking about a Samson
and Delilah-type haircut?

36:05.840 --> 36:10.050
Well, he didn't get a
chance to test his theory,

36:10.120 --> 36:12.009
but just in case he's right,

36:13.800 --> 36:15.450
let's take these for backup.

36:18.720 --> 36:20.085
Where do you want to do this?

36:20.160 --> 36:21.525
How about the quarry?

36:21.600 --> 36:23.762
Plenty of open ground.
Should work.

36:23.840 --> 36:25.126
Let's go.
(WIND HOWLING)

36:26.680 --> 36:28.125
(THUNDER CRACKLING)

36:56.280 --> 36:58.760
Okay, so...

36:59.240 --> 37:00.685
My book could have been wrong.

37:00.960 --> 37:02.325
(THUNDER CRACKLING)
(SHOUTING)

37:02.640 --> 37:03.641
(GASPS)

37:07.840 --> 37:09.490
(GRUNTING)

37:20.320 --> 37:21.321
Behind you!

37:24.120 --> 37:25.326
(GRUNTS)

37:26.200 --> 37:28.328
(BOTH GROWLING)

37:28.920 --> 37:30.126
(GRUNTING)

37:30.840 --> 37:32.171
(GROWLING)

37:52.360 --> 37:54.203
What do we do now?
Get to their hair.

37:54.280 --> 37:56.521
Easier said than...
(SCREAMING) (GROWLING)

38:01.360 --> 38:02.361
Come on!

38:03.080 --> 38:04.081
Damn it!

38:04.600 --> 38:05.965
(GRUNTING)

38:10.200 --> 38:11.201
MONROE: I'll take
the one on the right.

38:11.280 --> 38:12.680
NICK: I'll take
the one on the left.

38:15.880 --> 38:17.689
What about the really
big guy in the middle?

38:18.040 --> 38:19.405
(GROWLING)

38:34.840 --> 38:36.171
Get off my son!

38:36.240 --> 38:37.571
(GROWLING)

39:16.040 --> 39:17.041
Dad.

39:17.320 --> 39:18.845
(GROWLING)

39:23.200 --> 39:24.440
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

39:26.880 --> 39:28.848
You didn't know what
you were up against.

39:30.440 --> 39:32.283
If I... Even if you
are friends with a Grimm,

39:32.360 --> 39:34.010
I couldn't see you die.

39:35.440 --> 39:36.805
How did you know
how to kill them?

39:36.920 --> 39:37.967
We didn't.

39:38.600 --> 39:40.329
Nick's ancestors did.

39:41.280 --> 39:42.930
I didn't think it was possible

39:43.280 --> 39:45.203
to fight on the same side
as a Grimm.

39:45.320 --> 39:47.641
I told you, he's different.

39:48.080 --> 39:49.923
Some things you have
to see for yourself.

39:51.800 --> 39:53.928
All my life, I've heard
about these guys.

39:54.640 --> 39:58.247
Your great grandfather,
whenever it would storm,

40:00.000 --> 40:01.206
he'd get scared.

40:01.760 --> 40:04.809
He told us kids, if the
Wildesheers ever came back,

40:06.280 --> 40:09.523
it meant something really
bad was going to come next.

40:10.720 --> 40:12.404
MONROE: How "really bad"?

40:12.520 --> 40:14.090
I don't know.

40:15.240 --> 40:18.244
Just something, somewhere,
was going to happen

40:18.320 --> 40:19.810
that would change the world.

40:20.600 --> 40:22.045
(THUNDER CRACKLING)

40:41.800 --> 40:43.404
Thank you.

40:43.520 --> 40:44.806
MAN: Any more food?

40:44.960 --> 40:47.770
No. It was good, though.

40:49.200 --> 40:50.565
(SIGHS)

40:56.440 --> 40:57.851
(GASPS) Ahh!

40:58.120 --> 40:59.610
(PANTING)

41:00.160 --> 41:01.446
Oh, God.
What?

41:02.160 --> 41:03.889
I think it's coming.

41:04.160 --> 41:05.491
(SCREAMING)

41:15.960 --> 41:17.440
JULIETTE: Can I have
the peas, please?

41:33.960 --> 41:36.964
Well, this wedding stuff
is pretty exciting, huh?

41:37.400 --> 41:38.845
Have you guys set a date yet?

41:42.080 --> 41:43.241
(SNARLS)

41:48.760 --> 41:49.966
What?

41:50.040 --> 41:51.644
Everybody just calm down.

41:51.800 --> 41:52.801
Okay?

42:04.920 --> 42:06.126
(SIGHS)

42:06.760 --> 42:07.807
Sorry.

42:09.440 --> 42:13.286
This is just gonna take
a little getting used to.
